content: 'ACID MAN' AT ATM:  The same guy has come up behind 2, different women at a #Citibank ATM (same East Side bank) demanding money--and threatening to throw acid in their faces, if they didn't come up with the cash. The first victim--22 years old--handed over the maximum withdrawal allowed, $1,000. In the second case, Monday May 29th, the 36 year old victim gave the guy $500.  The address is 1266 First Avenue, Manhattan.

5 YEAR OLD SHOT IN HEAD...ON BIRTHDAY!
The little boy is adorable; Jaheen Hunter was walking out of a Bronx apartment building Monday, after celebrating his 5th birthday with his father. A stray bullet hit him. On Tuesday, U.S. Marshals arrested Michael "White Boy" Quiles. ****One piece of good news: We're hearing the bullet lodged in Jaheen's skull and did not cause brain damage.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery
title: Timeline Photos

content:
HUSBAND OF NBC EXEC CHARGED WiTH KILLING THEIR 7 YEAR OLD DAUGHTER:
This is a heartbreaking story. Gabrielle White was just 7 years old. Her mother, Michelle Hord-White, is Vice President of Talent Acquisition for NBC Network. Hord-White's estranged husband, Neil White, is now charged with suffocating their little girl at his New Rochelle home Tuesday. A nanny found the child dead in bed. When police responded to the home, they found Neil White's wrists were slit, perhaps due to an attempted suicide attempt. After he was treated at a local hospital, White was charged with murder in the 2nd degree.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery
title: Timeline Photos

content: 'WHITE BOY' CHARGED WITH SHOOTING 5 YEAR OLD BIRTHDAY CHILD IN HEAD:  A hulking Michael (White Boy) Quiles was walked out of a Bronx police precinct Tuesday night, charged with nearly killing 5 year old #JaheenHunter.  Jaheen was leaving an apartment building Monday with his dad, on the little boy's 5th birthday, when a stray bullet hit him in the head. Quilies allegedly apologized to the victim's dad, saying "Sorry, Charlie," before running away. The latest reports say the bullet actually DID pass through Jaheen's brain and lodged in his skull. A family vigil for the child continues at New York-Presbyterian Hospital, where he remains in very critical condition.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery

content:
DADDY DID IT:  POLICE This is the mug shot from the Westchester County DA's office, after 47 year old Neil White was charged with suffocating his 7 year old daughter, Gabrielle. 
The 2nd grader was found in her bed Tuesday by a babysitter, after the sitter showed up at the father's New Rochelle home about 3 pm and encountered Neil White, who had slit wrists. The girl's mother is  Michelle Hord-White, an executive at NBC. Hord-White had filed for divorce in April and the couple shared custody of the child. PIX 11 will have a "live" report from New Rochelle at 5 PM.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery
title: Timeline Photos

content: TEARS FOR GABRIELLE; DAUGHTER OF NBC EXEC ALLEGEDLY KILLED BY FATHER: Police in New Rochelle, New York, have accused the father of 7 year old, Gabrielle White, with suffocating her--when the 2nd grader visited his home.  Gabrielle's mother is an executive with NBC Network, Michelle Hord-White.  The New York Times covered her wedding to Neil White in 2007.  Hord-White had filed for divorce from her husband in April.  The estranged couple was sharing custody of their daughter. Nicole Johnson filed this report for PIX 11 News at 5 PM.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery

Barron has finished his school year in New York and will start a new school in the Washington, D.C. area.  This video shows the First Family exiting Marine 1. She said she was looking forward to the memories the family would be making in its new home.

content: DRAGGED COP; DEEP TROUBLE:  The NYPD booked Justin Murrell Friday for allegedly dragging an NYPD cop 3 blocks, using a stolen car, and leaving Officer #DalshVeve in a coma. This happened on June 3rd in #EastFlatbush, Brooklyn. Officer Murrell managed to squeeze off two shots, while he was being dragged, hitting Murrell in the face.  Now that Murrell's been treated in the hospital, he is being charged, at 15, with attempted murder and assault.  He's already got a lengthy rap sheet as an alleged member of Eight Trey Crips gang.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery

content: SUICIDE BY TEXT:  #GUILTY!  Michelle Carter, the 20 year old Massachusetts woman accused of urging her troubled boyfriend to commit suicide, was found guilty this morning of involuntary manslaughter.  A judge rendered the verdict, after a bench trial.  In July 2014, Carter had sent 100's of texts to her boyfriend, who was grappling with suicidal thoughts.  18 year old Conrad Roy inhaled carbon monoxide in his pickup truck to kill himself.  Prosecutors said Michelle Carter listened by phone to Roy's last breaths. The brief clip here has the judge allowing Carter to remain free on bail, until she's sentenced.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery

content: JERSEY SHORE TRAGEDY FOR 2, YOUNG COUSINS:  13 year old Mitzi Hernandez was not strong enough for the rough surf in Belmar, NJ on Thursday--the day before her final day of school this year. Good Samaritans could not save her, when they found her in the water. Her 12 year old cousin, Emily, is now on life support.  Christie Duffy of PIX 11 went to #Belmar Friday to report on this #JerseyShore tragedy.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery

content: YO, THE BUS IS REVERSING!  Check out this cell phone clip of an MTA New York City Transit bus racing backwards for several city blocks, after the driver thought she had put the Q58 bus in park.  Turns out she had left the bus in NEUTRAL, and it started rolling backwards down a full, city block in Brooklyn, hitting 10, parked cars--and one guy changing a tire--before it FINALLY hit a fence outside St. Paul's Lutheran Church.  It came to a stop at Knickerbocker Avenue and Palmetto Street.  Luckily, the guy changing the tire wasn't badly hurt.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery

content: ONE PUNCH, YOU'RE DEAD:  But there's no law in #NewYork that treats a sucker-punch as a felony, if the victim ends up maimed or dead.  Since last June, several New Yorkers have been knocked into comas--or landed in the morgue--after getting sucker punched.  The perps are usually charged with 3rd degree assault, and the maximum jail time is often =far less= than a year.  The New York State Senate is trying to pass a new bill, named for victim Ildefonso Romero, Jr.  It would turn a sucker punch into a felony.  Romero's family did an extremely emotional interview with PIX 11.  Please watch and share your thoughts on the matter.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery

content:
$40,000 REWARD:  It's been nearly a year since an 18 year old college student from #Virginia stepped on a plastic bag, tucked into a Central Park boulder, and had his left foot blown up.  Connor Golden, who was on vacation from the University of Miami, had part of his left leg amputated at BELLEVUE HOSPITAL CENTER.  
The first anniversary is July 3rd.  Now, the NYPD wants people to submit their photos from that time of year near Central Park. Deputy Commissioner for Counter-Terrorism, John Miller, noted the explosive materials were similar to those used in the recent Manchester Arena bombing that killed 22 people.  Myles NM spoke to the federal ATF investigators, along with the NYPD Chief of Detectives.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery

content: SCREENING LAPTOPS =AND= AIRLINE EMPLOYEES:  John Kelly, the U.S. Secretary for the Department of #HomelandSecurity, announced new, #aviation security measures for airlines that have direct flights to the United States from overseas.  This affects about 2,000 commercial flights daily.  The measures call for enhanced screening of "personal electronic devices" and better VETTING of airport staff, before they're hired!  There will also be better measures for detection of "trace" explosives.
name: Mary Murphy Mystery
